15 WHEREAS, understanding the challenges faced by families in food deserts, she partnered
16 with Backpack Buddies to provide food for children over the weekends and collaborated with
17 a USDA sponsor to offer summer meals, ensuring that local children had reliable access to
18 nutritious food; and
19 WHEREAS, her perseverance, integrity, and compassion have earned her the admiration of
20 colleagues and community members alike, with many praising her as a trusted partner, an
21 empathetic leader, and a source of inspiration; and
22 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
23 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately honored.
24 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
25 the members of this body commend Kristen Timoteo, the Georgia Public Library Service's
26 2024 Library Employee of the Year, and extend sincere best wishes for future health,
27 happiness, and success.
28 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
29 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
30 Kristen Timoteo.
